Lagos State Police Command officers have arrested four fake soldiers. The operatives of the Iju Divison led by the DPO, CSP Gbenga Stephen, apprehended them. Public Relations Officer, SP Benjamin Hundeyin said they were caught in the Iju area on Sunday. The impersonators were moving in a Mazda 3 when the police stopped them. They are Samuel Abel – 28, Victor ljeemai – 35, Lukman Salabiu – 43 and Oyinyechi Macus – 30. The suspects have been transferred to the State Criminal Investigation Department (SCID) Yaba for further investigation.